        "speaker_id": "LibriTTS_R-5840",
        "content": "Schubert's most famous quartet is the one in D minor with the lovely slow movement, a theme with variations, the theme being his own song, \"Death and the Maiden.\" One of the greatest works in the whole range of chamber music is his string quintet with two violoncellos.",
